ats gets 64-bit counters from iptACCOUNT</li><li>changed more bit rate multipliers to 1000</li><li>polished Smoothinfo some more</li><li>ping6 and traceroute are now setuid root</li><li>updated USB and PCI IDs</li><li>libexpat is now built using DESTDIR; the old method shouldn't have worked</li><li>the system RC scripts now use flag files to communicate among themselves</li></ul><p style="margin:5pt 0 0 0"><i><sup>*</sup> Updating dhcpcd and directing startup messages to syslog necessitated changing most of the RC scripts in /etc/rc.d.</i></p><p style="margin:5pt 0 0 0"><b><u>Standard warning</u></b><br />Caution: This update includes changes to core components which will break some old-style 'homebrew' modifications or customisations and may leave your system inoperable. Newer mods which use only the available SmoothInstall methods will likely be unaffected. Check for updates in your mods' threads in <a href='http://community.smoothwall.org' target='blank'>the forum</a> before you apply this update.</p><p style="color:#c00000; text-align:center; margin:5pt 0 0 0"><b>Reboot after installing this update to ensure that all changes take effect.</b></p>|2015-08-21|http://community.smoothwall.org/forum/viewtopic.php?t=42246|20630525
